ABSTRACT
Methods and apparatuses are provided for wireless commu-
nications. Configuration information including a resource
start offset and information for a transmission type of an
enhanced physical downlink control channel (EPDCCH) are
transmitted. Downlink control information (DCI) is trans-
mitted to a user equipment (UE) using at least one antenna
port of a base station on the EPDCCH using at least one of
control channel elements (CCES). A resource of a physical
uplink control channel (PUCCH) is determined based on a
first CCE of the at least one of CCE, information in the DCI,
and the resource start offset in the configuration information,
if the transmission type of the EPDCCH is distributed
transmission. A hybrid automatic repeat request acknowl-
edgement (HARQ-ACK) signal is received on the deter-
mined resource.
